subject:

HELP FROM GOD IS LASTING AND COMPLETE
===================================================================
verse:

Verse for today: Don’t put your confidence in powerful
people there is No help for you there. (Ps. 146:3) - (read
Ps. 146) 

===================================================================
reflection:

The psalmist portrays powerful people as inadequate saviors,
making false promises they cannot deliver (Ps. 146:3). God
is the hope and the help of the needy. Jesus confirms His
concern for the poor and afflicted in (Lk. 4:18-21). He does
not separate the physical needs from the spiritual needs but
attends to both. While God not the government, is the hope
of the needy, we are His instruments to help here on earth.

===================================================================
prayer:

Lord God, Psalm 146:3 reminds us not to put our trust in
powerful people, for they cannot save or truly help us.
Instead, You alone are our hope and refuge, caring deeply
for the needy and afflicted. Help us to rely fully on Your
strength and serve as Your hands to help those in need,
reflecting Jesus' compassion for the whole person-both
physical and spiritual. May we faithfully be instruments of
Your love and mercy in this world. Amen. (Al)

===================================================================
